## Wind shader

Wind belongs in the vertex shader. Community Bevy grass experiments likewise recommend shader-side bending rather than modifying thousands of blade meshes on the CPU. ([Reddit][4])

A blade needs a normalized height value:

```text
0.0 at root
1.0 at tip
```

Then apply increasing displacement toward the tip:

```wgsl
let root_weight = vertex_height * vertex_height;

let phase =
    dot(world_position.xz, vec2<f32>(0.07, 0.09))
    + time * wind_speed
    + instance.wind_phase;

let wind = sin(phase) * wind_strength;

world_position.x += wind * root_weight;
world_position.z += wind * 0.35 * root_weight;
```

Add two frequencies:

```text
Low frequency:
large field-wide gusts

High frequency:
small blade flutter
```

Also vary gust intensity using a world-space noise texture so the entire grass field does not sway identically.

