## Terrain alignment

Grass blades should normally grow upward relative to gravity, not straight out from the terrain normal.

Use the terrain normal primarily to:

* Position the root.
* Slightly tilt the blade.
* Reject excessive slopes.
* Orient low ground-cover clusters.

For ordinary tall grass:

```text
70–90% world-up orientation
10–30% surface-normal influence
```

Otherwise grass on a hillside looks pasted perpendicular to the slope.

