## Chunk and LOD organization

I recommend:

```rust
#[derive(Component)]
pub struct GrassPatch {
    pub terrain_chunk: ChunkCoord,
    pub species_set: GrassSpeciesSetId,
    pub instance_count: u32,
    pub lod: GrassLod,
}
```

Suggested ranges for your RTX 3070 target:

| Range    | Representation                    |
| -------- | --------------------------------- |
| 0–25 m   | Segmented blades or rich clusters |
| 25–70 m  | Simple instanced quads/clusters   |
| 70–140 m | Sparse low-detail clusters        |
| Beyond   | Terrain shader detail only        |

These are starting points, not guaranteed budgets. Actual density should be determined through GPU profiling.

Cull at patch level first. Later, use GPU-side instance culling if patch overdraw becomes expensive.

