## Materials and transparency

Grass transparency can be expensive because alpha blending creates sorting and overdraw problems.

Prefer:

* Alpha masking/cutout.
* Alpha-to-coverage when multisampling is enabled.
* Opaque procedural blade geometry for stylized grass.
* Minimal overlapping cards.

For dense tropical grass, actual thin geometry often behaves better than heavily layered transparent cards.

Use two-sided rendering carefully. Rendering both sides is usually necessary for grass cards, but it doubles relevant fragment work. Alternatively, create blade geometry with controlled facing and normals.

